  <title translate="true">MT-POP-Backlash</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">Motion Definition:<keyword translate="true">Backlash</keyword><keyword translate="true">Lash</keyword><keyword translate="true">Lost-motion</keyword><keyword translate="true">Play</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="" style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.00; background-color:transparent; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1" style="width:500px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Backlash:</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> a physical gap between two machine elements that transmit a force or torque between each other. </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Backlash</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is usually detrimental to the performance of the machine. After </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Backlash</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is traversed, the two machine component have different velocities - and there is an </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Impact" styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">impact</link><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">. However, in special circumstances, backlash may reduce residual vibration!</text></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso-small"><text styleclass="SeeAlso-small" translate="true">Other names: Play, Lash</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> (especially with auto-engines),</text><text styleclass="SeeAlso-small" translate="true"> Lost-motion.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
